'''Jorge Andrés Carrascal Guardo''' (born 25 May 1998) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]], Carrascal was a [[Millonarios F.C.|Millonarios]] youth graduate, after starting it out at CD Heroicos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.primertiempo.co/2016/03/el-cartagenero-jorge-carrascal-en-los.html|title=El cartagenero Jorge Carrascal, en los planes del Sevilla|date=3 March 2016|trans-title=''Cartagenero'' Jorge Carrascal, in Sevilla's target|publisher=Primer Tiempo|language=es|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> He made his professional – and [[Categoría Primera A]] – debut on 9 November 2014 at the age of only 16, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Luis Hernán Mosquera]] in a 1–0 away loss against [[Deportes Tolima]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardia.com/deportes/futbol-colombiano/286491-deportes-tolima-supero-1-0-a-millonarios|title=Deportes Tolima superó 1–0 a Millonarios|trans-title=Deportes Tolima defeated Millonarios by 1–0|publisher=[[Vanguardia Liberal]]|language=es|date=10 November 2014|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>

Carrascal only appeared again 7 November 2015, again from the bench in a 2–0 loss at [[Independiente Medellín]]. His first (and only) start for the club came on 17 March 2016, in a 2–0 [[Copa Colombia]] home win against [[Bogotá F.C.|Bogotá]].{{citation needed|date=March 2022}}

On 25 May 2016, Carrascal moved abroad, signing a five-year deal with Spanish [[La Liga]] side [[Sevilla FC]], being immediately assigned to [[Sevilla Atlético|the reserves]] in [[Segunda División]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/20160525/402039001055/el-sevilla-ficha-al-joven-colombiano-carrascal-millonarios-para-su-filial.html|title=El Sevilla ficha al joven colombiano Carrascal (Millonarios) para su filial|trans-title=Sevilla sign Colombian youngster Carrascal (Millonarios) for their reserves|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo (newspaper)|Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=25 May 2016|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>

On 13 July 2017, he transferred to [[Karpaty Lviv]] in Ukraine at first on loan for a year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://football.ua/ukraine/339323-karpaty-usililis-kolumbijjskim-poluzashhitnikom-iz-sevili.html|title=Карпаты усилились колумбийским полузащитником из Севильи}}</ref> In April 2018 Carrascal was recognized as a player of the month in the [[Ukrainian Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ua-football.com/ua/ukrainian/high/1525945873-viznacheno-naykraschogo-gravcya-kvitnya-v-upl.html|title = Визначено Найкращого гравця квітня в УПЛ|date = 10 May 2018}}</ref>

In 2021, Carrascal won the [[Argentine Primera División]] with [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].

On 18 February 2022, Carrascal joined [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] on loan from River Plate for the remainder of the [[2021–22 PFC CSKA Moscow season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Хорхе Карраскаль — в ПФК ЦСКА! |url=https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/khorkhe-karraskal-v-pfk-cska/ |website=pfc-cska.com/ |publisher=PFC CSKA Moscow |access-date=18 February 2022 |language=Russian |date=18 February 2022}}</ref> On 20 May 2022, CSKA confirmed that the purchase clause in the loan contract had been activated and Carrascal will be under contract with CSKA from the 2022–23 season until 2026.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CSKA Moscow|url=https://pfc-cska.com/novosti/vse-novosti/novosti-osnovy/karraskal-s-nami/|title=Карраскаль — с нами!|date=20 May 2022|accessdate=20 May 2022|language=ru}}</ref>

On 27 August 2023, Carrascal moved to [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]] and signed a four-year contract, with an optional fifth year.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Dynamo Moscow|url=https://fcdm.ru/news/xorxe-karraskal-peresel-v-dynamo/|title=Хорхе Карраскаль перешёл в "Динамо"|date=27 August 2023|language=ru}}</ref> He was voted player of the month by Dynamo's fans for March 2024.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Dynamo Moscow|url=https://fcdm.ru/news/xorxe-karraskal-vtb-igrok-mesiaca-v-marte/|title=Хорхе Карраскаль — ВТБ Игрок месяца в марте|date=6 April 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

On 2 August 2025, Carrascal signed a four-year contract with [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CR Flamengo|url=https://www.flamengo.com.br/noticias/futebol/jorge-carrascal-e-mais-um-reforco-do-mengao|title=Jorge Carrascal é mais um reforço do Mengão|trans-title=Jorge Carrascal is another reinforcement for Mengão|date=2 August 2025|access-date=2 August 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

